      <h1 class='title'>Service Children's Education Agency</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='commons-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HC Deb 02 December 2003 vol 415 c54WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_54ws' title='Col. 54WS &mdash; HC Deb 02 December 2003 vol 415 c54WS' name='column_54ws' href='#column_54ws' rel='bookmark'>54WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution'>
        <a name='S6CV0415P2_20031202_CWS_4'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-ivor-caplin' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0415P2_20031202_CWS_4' title='Link to this speech by Mr Ivor Caplin' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-ivor-caplin" title="Mr Ivor Caplin">The Parliamentary Under-Secretary of State for Defence (Mr. Ivor Caplin)</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para">I am today placing a copy of the Service Children's Education (SCE) agency Quinquennial Review Report in the Library of the House. The Review has examined the Agency in detail and concluded that SCE is delivering a good service to parents and children and that, as a core component of military life overseas, the balance of advantage lies with it remaining part of the MOD. Agency status was judged to have delivered benefits and have the scope to continue doing so through the ongoing target-setting regime. The Review identified a number of issues for further study and these will be taken forward by Chief Executive SCE who has the responsibility for overseeing the implementation of the Review's recommendations, most of which are specialist education issues.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
